        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#VM">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Εὐστάχι<supplied reason="omitted">ο</supplied>ς <hi rend="small"><expan><abbr><hi rend="ligature">ἤ</hi></abbr><ex>τε</ex></expan></hi> <hi rend="small">κ<choice><reg>αὶ</reg><orig>ὲ</orig></choice></hi> <hi rend="small">Βῶκυς</hi>
                    <lb n="2"/>ἐκοιμήθη
                    <lb n="3"/>εἰδοῖς Μαείες
                    <lb n="4"/>σώφρων καὶ ἀκα
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/>τάγνωστος ἔζησεν
                    <lb n="6"/>ἔτη <num value="35">λε</num>
                    <lb n="7"/>καὶ ἀνεπαύσατο
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text after Lo Faro in Marchese 2012</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="1-3">
                        <note>ἤκε and Βῶκυς are written smaller and adjoins the ends of ll. 1-3. Lo Faro (2012) agrees with Agnello (1950-1951) that the smaller text is an addition to the main text and is meant to specify the name of the deceased (vel quidem Bochus or Bucco).</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--Eustachis he ke (i.e. kai) Bokys (bwkus; i.e. Bokchos) ekoimethe eidois Maeies (i.e. Maiais) sophron kai akatagnostos; ezesen ete le' kai anepausato. The name Bokys is written smaller between l.2 and 3. It does not seem to be related to the rest of the text.--></p>
            </div>
